# Source for requirements.lock in this same directory -- ported verbatim
# from the old ~/Scripts/Self-hosted/OpenWebUI/configuration/variables/deps.sh's
# PYTHON_REQUIREMENTS. Small and static enough (unlike ComfyUI's, which
# depends on 69 nodes' own requirements.txt) to just hand-maintain here
# directly -- no Nix generation needed.
#
# To update: edit this file, then from within a shell that has
# python312Packages.pip-tools:
#
#   pip-compile --generate-hashes --allow-unsafe --resolver=backtracking \
#     --output-file=requirements.lock requirements.in
#
# then restart self-hosted-openwebui and run
# `systemctl start self-hosted-openwebui@install` to rebuild the venv
# against the new lock. See this repo's
# Nixos/modules/services/self-hosted/openwebui/info.md.

